other_tests.findings: There is a thickened appendix measuring 8 mm with surrounding fat stranding. There is some mild thickening of the cecal wall at the appendiceal orifice. Multiple diverticula are noted in the sigmoid colon, but there is no evidence of diverticulitis. A 3.0-cm septated hypodense lesion in segment IV of the liver, likely consistent with a septated cyst, and a 0.9-cm hypodense lesion in the left kidney, likely representing a simple cyst.
